{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/resize-images-linux/","webpackCompilationHash":"d8d062d8421ee54f0b4c","result":{"data":{"post":{"id":"9660ccb7-4472-5821-909d-40f37dd76e36","html":"<h3>The convert command can quickly resize an image directly on a linux terminal.</h3>\n<p>The following command will resize an image based on a percent of 50%:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">convert <span class=\"token operator\">-</span>resize <span class=\"token number\">50</span><span class=\"token operator\">%</span> example<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>jpg example<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>jpg</code></pre></div>\n<p>To resize an image forcing a width and height:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">convert example<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>jpg <span class=\"token operator\">-</span>resize <span class=\"token number\">200</span>x100 example<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>jpg</code></pre></div>\n<p>To resize an image keeping the aspect ratio and a width of 200:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">convert example<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>jpg <span class=\"token operator\">-</span>resize <span class=\"token number\">200</span> example<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>jpg</code></pre></div>\n<p>To resize an image keeping the aspect ratio an a height of 200:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">convert example<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>jpg <span class=\"token operator\">-</span>resize x200 example<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>jpg</code></pre></div>\n<p>To rotate an image, just specify the angle needed:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">convert example<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>jpg <span class=\"token operator\">-</span>rotate <span class=\"token number\">90</span> example<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>rotated<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>jpg</code></pre></div>","fields":{"slug":"/resize-images-linux/","prefix":"2019-09-28"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Using convert to resize and rotate images","author":"Bernardo Camargo","category":"unix","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/f804c22668986f456363f012b552622a/c83a6/sed.jpg"}}}}},"authornote":{"id":"8cf19e6f-22ca-5574-82f1-600a295f17f0","html":"<p><strong>Bernardo Camargo</strong> Just sharing some code insights that might help you out somehow!</p>"},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"facebook":{"appId":"591875029"}}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/resize-images-linux/","prev":{"id":"833d24e6-1f64-5b76-a87e-bacbc5a847a4","fields":{"slug":"/using-sed-linux/","prefix":"2019-09-27","source":"posts"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Using SED - A Stream EDitor for unix systems","category":"unix"}},"source":"posts"}}}